@kishoreg I didn't follow. We don't store the time boundary now. Why do we need to keep it in ZK?
Perhaps you are trying to support an arbitrary time boundary that a user can set. I don't see a use case for that now. My thought is that we can support one of two time boundaries -- either include the latest <day/hour> or exclude it. I think this will cover most of the use cases.

What is the use case to cover up to some arbitrary user-specified time?

@kishoreg 
Addressed the comment and updated the PR.
